{{Religious text primary}}
{{耶稣}}

[[File:KidronValleyFromOldCity.JPG|thumb]]

'''汲沦谷'''（[[汉语拼音|汉语拼音]]：Ji2 Lun2 Gu3；{{lang-he|'''נחל קדרון'''}}，''Naḥal Qidron''，'''Qidron Valley'''；{{lang-ar|'''وادي الجز'''}}，''Wadi al-Joz''；{{lang-en|'''Kidron Valley'''}}）是沿着[[耶路撒冷老城|耶路撒冷老城]]东城墙外的一道山谷，将[[圣殿山|圣殿山]]和[[橄榄山|橄榄山]]隔开，而从橄榄山再向东穿过[[犹大旷野|犹大旷野]]，就到达[[死海|死海]]。犹太居民点Kedar就得名于汲沦谷，位于汲沦谷上方的山脊；另一个居民点Wadi Al-Joz则采用了汲沦谷的阿拉伯语名称。在多雨的冬季，偶然的山洪暴发会在山谷中形成一条间歇性的溪流。

== 在圣经中 ==
《[[圣经|圣经]]》多次提及汲沦谷。汲沦谷是许多犹太人坟墓的所在，包括[[押沙龙墓|押沙龙墓]]、[[希悉子孙墓|希悉子孙墓]]和[[撒迦利亚墓|撒迦利亚墓]]。<!-- At one time, the water of the [[Gihon_Spring|Gihon Spring]] flowed through the valley, but it was diverted by [[Hezekiah's_tunnel|Hezekiah's tunnel]] to 供水给耶路撒冷。 -->

据《[[希伯来圣经|希伯来圣经]]》记载，在[[押沙龙|押沙龙]]造反期间，[[大卫王|大卫王]]通过汲沦谷逃走。

据《[[新约圣经|新约圣经]]》记载，[[耶稣|耶稣]]多次穿过汲沦谷往来于耶路撒冷和[[伯大尼|伯大尼]]之间。

<!-- === 末世论中的汲沦谷 ===
The Bible calls the valley "[[Valley_of_Jehoshaphat|Valley of Jehoshaphat]] - Emek Yehoshafat" ({{lang-he|עמק יהושפט}}), meaning "The valley where God will judge." It appears in Jewish [[Eschatology|Eschatologic]] prophecies, which include the return of [[以利亚|以利亚]], followed by the arrival of the [[Jewish_Messiah|Messiah]], and also the war of [[Gog_and_Magog|Gog and Magog]] and [[Judgment_day|Judgment day]]. According to the prophecies, in the war of Gog and Magog, the two major [[coalitions|coalitions]] of [[Goy|gentile]] nations will join forces against the Jewish state in Israel. Israel will be overwhelmed and conquered, and the last [[stronghold|stronghold]] will be [[耶路撒冷|耶路撒冷]], which will also be conquered by the gentiles. After the gentiles finally succeed and destroy Israel, God will commence Judgement. God will save Israel and battle "with diseases, rain, fire and stones" against all the gentile nations that set to destroy Israel, and will fill [[以色列地|以色列地]] with their bodies which will take the Jews 7 months to bury all. In the prophecies, it says he will bring the descendants of [[Ishmael|Ishmael]] down to Emek-Yehoshafat (Kidron vally), and then he will judge all of the gentiles for all of the wrong they have done against Israel since the beginning of time, and only the gentiles that helped Israel will be spared. -->

